# Trivy CVE suppressions.
#
# Production teams that scan images CANNOT avoid this file. Upstream base
# images often have known CVEs whose fixes are merged into the distro's
# next release but haven't been rebuilt into the base image yet. We are
# stuck waiting on the upstream rebuild — there is no patch we can apply
# in our Dockerfile.
#
# Rules of the game (real production teams follow these):
#   1. Every entry has an EXPIRATION date (`exp:`). Trivy fails the build
#      again when that date passes, forcing you to revisit instead of
#      letting an ignore rule rot forever.
#   2. Each entry has a Why: comment explaining the upstream context.
#   3. NEVER add MEDIUM/LOW CVEs to this file. The threshold is HIGH+.
#   4. Reviewed every quarter (mark in calendar).
#
# Current entries:

# Debian 12's libssl3 0.3.0.18 → 0.3.0.19 was released by upstream Debian
# but the gcr.io/distroless/nodejs20-debian12 image has not yet been
# rebuilt to incorporate the fix. Track upstream rebuild here:
#   https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/distroless/releases
# Re-check quarterly and remove these lines once the distroless rebuild lands.
# (Trivy `exp:` field tried but the trivy-action SARIF flow doesn't honor it
# reliably — workaround: no expiration field; track in calendar reminder.)
CVE-2026-31789
CVE-2026-28387
CVE-2026-28388
CVE-2026-28389
CVE-2026-28390

# libssl3 heap use-after-free in PKCS7_verify() (CVE-2026-45447, CVSS 9.8).
# Debian shipped the fix as 3.0.20-1~deb12u2, but the
# gcr.io/distroless/nodejs20-debian12 base has NOT been rebuilt yet.
# Verified 2026-06-18: the latest base digest (sha256:6fe218db...) still ships
# libssl3 3.0.18-1~deb12u2, so a `docker build --pull` does NOT clear it.
# Distroless has no package manager, so there is no Dockerfile-level patch we
# can apply — we are blocked on the upstream rebuild.
# Why low risk here: sample-app is an HTTP service that never calls
# PKCS7_verify()/processes S/MIME, so the vulnerable code path is unreachable.
# Track upstream rebuild: https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/distroless/releases
# Re-check quarterly and REMOVE this line once the distroless rebuild lands.
CVE-2026-45447
